NotesEn: Retiring with the rank of Captain.
Promoted Commander in 1982 when he was at the Canadian Land Force Command and Staff College. Transferred to Ottawa in 1983. Promoted Captain in January 1986. Retired 1989.

First woman to earn the qualification.

Awarded the Order of Military Merit in 1995.

Appointed Commander Officer, becoming the first woman to command a Canadian Forces flying squadron.

Served in Afghanistan and the Balkans.

Awarded the Gulf and Kuwait Medal, the General Campaign Star, the Special Service Medal (MSS) and the Canadian Forces Decoration (CD).
Graduated in 1995 from the Royal Military College in Kingston.

OrganizationLongEn: Royal Canadian Air Force 8 Wing (Trenton, Ontario)
NotesEn: Rescue Coordination Centre on search and rescue operations

OrganizationLongEn: Royal Canadian Air Force 17 Wing (Winnipeg, Manitoba)
Royal Canadian Air Force 423 Squadron (Shearwater, Nova Scotia)
NotesEn: Awarded the Canadian Forces Decoration (C.D.) and the Sikorsky Helicopter Rescue Award.

OrganizationLongEn: 3rd Field Artillery Regiment (The Loyal Company), 5th Canadian Division

NotesEn:
Served in Bosnia and in Afghanistan three times. Awarded the following honours:
Order of Military Merit
Meritorious Service Medal
Southwest Asia Service Medal (Afghanistan)
General Campaign Star (Afghanistan)
Mention in Dispatch
Canadian Peacekeeping Service Medal
NATO Service Medal (Bosnia)
Canadian Forces' Decoration
US Army Commendation Medal
With the 6 Jim Whitecross Royal Canadian Air Cadet Squadron
Three-year investiture, serving in the capacity as Honorary Colonel for the Air Staff located at National Defence Headquarters in Ottawa.
